text: Joseph Chatelus (born 2 December 1908, date of death unknown) was a French bobsledder who competed in the early 1950s. At the 1952 Winter Olympics in Oslo, he finished 11th in the four-man event and 17th in the two-man events. ==References== *1952 bobsleigh two-man results *1952 bobsleigh four-man results *Bobsleigh four-man result: 1948-64 *Joseph Chatelus' profile at Sports Reference.com Category:Bobsledders at the 1952 Winter Olympics Category:French male bobsledders Category:1908 births Category:Year of death missing
